<title type="html"><![CDATA[Reorganization of the code.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=54&amp;p=286#p286"><![CDATA[
You can &quot;attach&quot; styles to elements which have neither <span style="font-weight: bold">class</span> nor <span style="font-weight: bold">id</span> attributes by using the element name. For example, to prevent all <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;h1&gt;</span> elements from using bold formatting:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>h1 &#123;<br /> font-weight: normal;<br />&#125;</code></dd></dl>To do this for all headings:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 &#123;<br /> font-weight: normal;<br />&#125;</code></dd></dl>These are called <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/selector.html#type-selectors" class="postlink">type selectors</a>. They are very neat (imho) and very widely supported.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=27">Cerbera</a> — Thu May 17, 2007 5:14 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
