<title type="html"><![CDATA[Reorganization of the code.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=54&amp;p=279#p279"><![CDATA[
Browsers can already disable styles and scripts. It's not really implemented by searching for &lt;script&gt; or &lt;style&gt; elements, but rather simply disabling scripting altogether or ignoring all author-level style sheets at the style processing level.<br /><br />Also note that &lt;script&gt; and &lt;style&gt; elements can be in the body too, and SVG also has &lt;script&gt; and &lt;style&gt; elements, and scripts can occur in javascript&#058; URIs, and links to stylesheets can also be in HTTP Link: headers or xml-stylesheet processing instructions, and you would want to disable those too if you disabled styling or scripting. So grouping the links that occur in the HEAD in HTML wouldn't really help anyway.<br /><br />Oh, almost forgot, they can occur in style=&quot;&quot; attributes and event handler attributes (e.g. onclick=&quot;&quot;), too.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Thu May 17, 2007 12:03 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
