<title type="html"><![CDATA[Reorganization of the code.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=54&amp;p=277#p277"><![CDATA[
It would offer no immediate benefits, but it could be used in the future to more-easily filter through the <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;head&gt;</span>. For example, a UA could disable scripts by blocking everything in the <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;headgroup title=&quot;scripts&quot;&gt;</span> rather than searching through the entire <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;head&gt;</span> for <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;script&gt;</span>. Also, this would force designers to group styles, scripts, and author information together. I'm not positive, but in my opinion, this would speed up disabling of features such as scripts and styles and also make it simpler.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=94">bfrohs</a> — Wed May 16, 2007 11:42 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
